    "summary": "Illustrates the two-phase process of dynamic server discovery and registration: initial system startup configuration loading and subsequent runtime additio",
    "whatItShows": "This diagram details the two primary flows for dynamic server discovery and registration. The first path outlines how servers are initialized and registered during system startup, involving configuration loading, parsing, filtering, dynamic class loading, and auto-connection. The second path describes the process for adding new server configurations at runtime, including dynamic class loading, registry addition, and server connection to update the system.",
    "whenToUse": "Use this diagram when designing systems that require dynamic component loading, pluggable architectures, or service discovery mechanisms where components (servers, plugins, modules) need to be discovered and registered either at startup or during runtime.",
